<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
<h1>1. Executive Summary</h1>
<p>TirePro is a full-stack web-based business management system purpose-built for the tyre industry in Pakistan. It enables tyre retailers, wholesalers, franchise networks, and distributors to manage their complete business operations from a single platform — covering sales, purchasing, inventory, customer/supplier accounts, financial ledger, and reporting.</p>

<h3>Core Capabilities</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>Multi-Organization / Multi-Branch:</b> One installation supports many independent businesses, each with multiple branches. Data is fully isolated per organization.</li>
  <li><b>Sales &amp; Invoicing:</b> Create sales invoices, track payment status, generate PDF invoices, bulk import via Excel.</li>
  <li><b>Purchase Orders:</b> Manage supplier POs, receive stock, track payment to suppliers.</li>
  <li><b>Inventory Management:</b> Real-time tyre stock levels, low-stock alerts, cost/sale price margins.</li>
  <li><b>Financial Ledger:</b> Banking-style accounts receivable and accounts payable per customer/supplier with running balance statements.</li>
  <li><b>Reports:</b> P&amp;L summary, brand performance, monthly revenue/profit charts.</li>
  <li><b>Settings:</b> Per-organization configuration — invoice prefixes, tax rates, currency, company profile.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Technology Stack</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Frontend</td><td>React 19 + TypeScript + Vite</td><td>SPA, component-based UI</td></tr>
  <tr><td>UI Library</td><td>Tailwind CSS + Lucide Icons</td><td>Styling &amp; icons</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Charts</td><td>Recharts</td><td>Dashboard &amp; Reports visualizations</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PDF Generation</td><td>jsPDF + html2canvas</td><td>Invoice PDF download</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Backend</td><td>Node.js + Express.js</td><td>REST API server</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Database</td><td>Microsoft SQL Server (MSSQL)</td><td>Persistent data store</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Authentication</td><td>bcryptjs (password hashing)</td><td>Secure login</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Data Import</td><td>xlsx (SheetJS)</td><td>Excel bulk import</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE -->
<h1>2. System Architecture Overview</h1>

<h3>High-Level Architecture</h3>
<div class="mockup">
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    BROWSER (React SPA)                      │
│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌───────────┐  │
│  │ Sidebar  │  │  Header  │  │  Pages   │  │BottomNav  │  │
│  │  (Nav)   │  │ (Search) │  │(Modules) │  │ (Mobile)  │  │
│  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └───────────┘  │
│         │              │           │                        │
│         └──────────────┴───────────┘                        │
│                        │                                    │
│              api/client.ts (fetch wrapper)                  │
│         X-Org-ID header + X-Branch-ID header                │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │ HTTP / REST API
┌──────────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────┐
│                   NODE.JS / EXPRESS SERVER                   │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  context.js: reads X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID headers    │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
│  Routes: /auth /sales /purchases /inventory /customers       │
│          /suppliers /ledger /payments /settings              │
│          /organizations /branches /products /lookups         │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │ mssql (tedious)
┌──────────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────┐
│                  SQL SERVER DATABASE                         │
│  organizations  branches  users  settings                    │
│  customers  suppliers  tires  products  tire_types           │
│  sales  sale_items  sale_payments                            │
│  purchases  purchase_items  purchase_payments                │
│  ledger_entries                                              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘</div>

<h3>Context Propagation</h3>
<p>Every API call from the frontend includes two custom headers:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>X-Org-ID</code>: The organization ID stored in <code>localStorage.orgId</code> after login.</li>
  <li><code>X-Branch-ID</code>: The branch ID stored in <code>localStorage.branchId</code> after login.</li>
</ul>
<p>The server reads these via <code>context.js → getContext(req)</code> and scopes all database queries to that organization/branch. Default fallback is <code>1</code> for backward compatibility.</p>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 3. MULTI-TENANCY MODEL -->
<h1>3. Multi-Tenancy Model</h1>

<h3>Three-Level Hierarchy</h3>
<div class="mockup">
Platform (TirePro installation)
  └── Organization (Business entity, e.g. "Ahmed Tyre Works")
        ├── Branch 1 (e.g. "Main Branch – Lahore")
        ├── Branch 2 (e.g. "Karachi Branch")
        └── Branch 3 (e.g. "Islamabad Branch")
              └── Users (role: org_admin | branch_manager | cashier | staff)</div>

<h3>Supported Business Models</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Configuration</th><th>User Setup</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Single shop, single location</td><td>1 Organization, 1 Branch</td><td>1 org_admin user</td></tr>
  <tr><td>One business, multiple branches</td><td>1 Organization, N Branches</td><td>org_admin + per-branch staff</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Multiple businesses (franchise/group)</td><td>N Organizations, each with N Branches</td><td>Separate org_admin per org</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Data Scoping Rules</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Scoped By</th><th>Tables</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Customers, Suppliers</td><td>Organization only</td><td>customers, suppliers</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Products, Tire Types</td><td>Organization only</td><td>products, tire_types</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Settings, Company Profile</td><td>Organization only</td><td>settings</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Inventory (Tires)</td><td>Organization + Branch</td><td>tires</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sales, Purchases</td><td>Organization + Branch</td><td>sales, purchases</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Payments, Ledger Entries</td><td>Organization + Branch</td><td>sale_payments, purchase_payments, ledger_entries</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ledger Statements</td><td>Organization-wide (all branches)</td><td>JOIN across branches</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Role Definitions</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Role</th><th>branch_id</th><th>Access Level</th></tr>
  <tr><td>org_admin</td><td>NULL (picks branch at login)</td><td>Full access to all branches within org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>branch_manager</td><td>Assigned branch ID</td><td>Full access to assigned branch only</td></tr>
  <tr><td>cashier</td><td>Assigned branch ID</td><td>Sales &amp; payment operations only</td></tr>
  <tr><td>staff</td><td>Assigned branch ID</td><td>Read-only + basic operations</td></tr>
</table>

