<h3>Login Form Fields</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Validation</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Email Address</td><td>email</td><td>Yes</td><td>Must contain '@'</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Password</td><td>password (toggleable)</td><td>Yes</td><td>Non-empty</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Login Workflow</h3>
<ol>
  <li>User enters email + password, clicks "Sign In"</li>
  <li>Client calls <code>POST /api/auth/login</code></li>
  <li>Server hashes and compares password with bcrypt</li>
  <li>On success, server returns: <code>id, name, email, role, organization_id, branch_id, organization{name,code,currency}, branches[]</code></li>
  <li>Client stores <code>orgId</code> and <code>branchId</code> in <code>localStorage</code></li>
  <li>App renders the main layout with <code>AuthUser</code> state set</li>
</ol>

<div class="info"><b>Rate Limiting:</b> Login endpoint is rate-limited to 10 attempts per 15 minutes per IP to prevent brute-force attacks.</div>

