<h1>7. Sales Module</h1>

<h2>7.1 UI Mockup — Sales List</h2>
<div class="mockup">
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Sales                                                          │
│  Manage customer sales and invoices                             │
├──────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┤
│ Total Sales  │  Collected   │  Outstanding                      │
│ PKR 485,000  │  PKR 360,000 │  PKR 125,000                     │
│  50 invoices │              │                                   │
├──────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────────────────────────┤
│ [🔍 Search invoice or customer]  [All ▼]  [Import] [New Sale+] │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Invoice#  │Date    │Customer  │Total    │Paid │Bal  │Status│Act│
├───────────┼────────┼──────────┼─────────┼─────┼─────┼──────┼───┤
│INV-24-001 │Jan 15  │Ahmed     │8,500    │8,500│  0  │●Paid │👁🖨⬇│
│INV-24-002 │Jan 16  │Bilal     │12,000   │6,000│6,000│◑Part │👁🖨⬇💳│
│INV-24-003 │Jan 17  │Tariq     │5,500    │  0  │5,500│○Pend │👁🖨⬇💳│
│INV-24-004 │Jan 10  │Kamran    │9,000    │  0  │9,000│●Over │👁🖨⬇💳│
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘</div>

<h2>7.2 Status Definitions</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Status</th><th>Color</th><th>Meaning</th><th>Transition Rules</th></tr>
  <tr><td>pending</td><td><span class="badge badge-amber">Amber</span></td><td>Invoice created, no payment</td><td>Auto → partial (when payment &lt; total); Manual → overdue, paid</td></tr>
  <tr><td>partial</td><td><span class="badge badge-blue">Blue</span></td><td>Some payment received</td><td>Auto → paid (when payment ≥ total)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>paid</td><td><span class="badge badge-green">Emerald</span></td><td>Fully settled</td><td>Manual → overdue (if needed)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>overdue</td><td><span class="badge badge-red">Red</span></td><td>Payment past due date</td><td>Auto → partial/paid on payment; Manual → pending</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7.3 New Sale Modal — Form Fields</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Customer</td><td>Searchable dropdown</td><td>Yes</td><td>Searches customer name/code</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Date</td><td>date</td><td>Yes</td><td>Defaults to today</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Status</td><td>select</td><td>Yes</td><td>Defaults to org's default_sale_status setting</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Notes</td><td>text</td><td>No</td><td>Free text, appears on invoice</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Line Items – Tire/Product</td><td>Searchable dropdown</td><td>Yes (min 1)</td><td>Searches tires (brand/model/size) + products</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Line Items – Qty</td><td>number</td><td>Yes</td><td>Min 1; deducted from stock on save</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Line Items – Unit Price</td><td>decimal</td><td>Yes</td><td>Pre-fills from tire/product sale_price</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Tax Rate (%)</td><td>number</td><td>No</td><td>Defaults from org settings</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7.4 Sales Business Rules</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Creating a sale decrements stock for each tire line item (stock = stock − qty)</li>
  <li>Deleting a sale restores stock for each tire line item</li>
  <li>Invoice number auto-generated: <code>[InvoicePrefix]-[YEAR]-[NNN]</code> (e.g. INV-2024-001)</li>
  <li>Invoice prefix and numbering sequence are per-organization settings</li>
  <li>amount_paid and status fields are automatically recalculated when payments are recorded or deleted</li>
</ul>

<h2>7.5 Payment Recording (PaymentModal)</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Amount</td><td>decimal</td><td>Yes</td><td>Must be &gt; 0</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Payment Date</td><td>date</td><td>Yes</td><td>Defaults to today</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Payment Method</td><td>select</td><td>Yes</td><td>Cash, Bank Transfer, Cheque, Card</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Reference No</td><td>text</td><td>No</td><td>Cheque / transfer reference</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Notes</td><td>text</td><td>No</td><td>Free text</td></tr>
</table>
<p>On payment record: updates <code>sales.amount_paid</code> and <code>sales.status</code>; inserts row into <code>sale_payments</code> and <code>ledger_entries</code> in a single SQL transaction.</p>

<h2>7.6 Excel Import Format</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Required</th><th>Format</th></tr>
  <tr><td>customer_name</td><td>Yes</td><td>Exact match to customer name in system</td></tr>
  <tr><td>date</td><td>Yes</td><td>YYYY-MM-DD</td></tr>
  <tr><td>item_name</td><td>Yes</td><td>Exact match to tire (brand+model+size) or product name</td></tr>
  <tr><td>qty</td><td>Yes</td><td>Integer</td></tr>
  <tr><td>unit_price</td><td>Yes</td><td>Decimal</td></tr>
  <tr><td>status</td><td>No</td><td>pending / paid / partial / overdue</td></tr>
  <tr><td>notes</td><td>No</td><td>Text</td></tr>
</table>

