<h2>14.2 P&amp;L Calculation</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Formula / Data Source</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Total Revenue</td><td>SUM(sales.total) for org+branch (all statuses except possibly cancelled)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Cost of Goods</td><td>SUM(purchases.total) WHERE status = 'received' for org+branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Gross Profit</td><td>Revenue − Cost of Goods</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Gross Margin %</td><td>(Gross Profit / Revenue) × 100</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 15. SETTINGS -->
<h1>15. Settings Module</h1>

<h2>15.1 Tab 1: Company Profile</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Used In</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Company Name</td><td>text</td><td>Invoice header, PDF</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Tagline</td><td>text</td><td>Invoice sub-header</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Address</td><td>textarea</td><td>Invoice header</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Phone</td><td>text</td><td>Invoice header</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Email</td><td>email</td><td>Invoice header</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Announcement</td><td>textarea</td><td>NewsBanner top of every page</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>15.2 Tab 2: Invoice &amp; PO Defaults</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Setting Key</th><th>Field</th><th>Default</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr><td>invoice_prefix</td><td>Invoice Prefix</td><td>INV</td><td>INV-2024-001 number format</td></tr>
  <tr><td>po_prefix</td><td>PO Prefix</td><td>PO</td><td>PO-2024-001 number format</td></tr>
  <tr><td>default_tax_rate</td><td>Default Tax Rate (%)</td><td>15</td><td>Pre-fills tax in new sale form</td></tr>
  <tr><td>payment_due_days</td><td>Payment Due (days)</td><td>30</td><td>Future: due date calculation</td></tr>
  <tr><td>currency</td><td>Currency Code</td><td>PKR</td><td>Displayed on all money values</td></tr>
  <tr><td>default_sale_status</td><td>Default Sale Status</td><td>pending</td><td>Pre-fills status in new sale form</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>15.3 Tab 3: Products (Non-Tire Items)</h2>
<p>Products are non-tire items that can be added as line items in sales and purchases (e.g. services, accessories, valves, wheel balancing).</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Code</td><td>text</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Name</td><td>text</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Category</td><td>text</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Unit</td><td>text</td><td>No (e.g. pcs, set, hr)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Cost Price</td><td>decimal</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Sale Price</td><td>decimal</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Description</td><td>text</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Active</td><td>checkbox</td><td>Yes (default: checked)</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>15.4 Tab 4: Lookup Tables (Tire Types)</h2>
<p>Tire types are used as a classification for inventory tires. Examples: Passenger Car, SUV/4x4, Truck/Commercial, Motorcycle, Agriculture, OTR.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Add new type: type name in text field + click "Add"</li>
  <li>Edit: click edit icon → inline input → Save or Cancel</li>
  <li>Delete: click delete icon (no confirmation required)</li>
  <li>Tire types are org-scoped (each org has its own list)</li>
</ul>

<h2>15.5 Settings Save Behavior</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Tab 1 and Tab 2 have a persistent "Save Changes" footer bar</li>
  <li>Changes not auto-saved; unsaved changes shown with unsaved indicator</li>
  <li>On save: <code>POST /api/settings</code> with all key-value pairs; server uses MERGE (upsert)</li>
  <li>Settings are cached client-side via <code>appSettings.ts</code> for use in PDF generation</li>
</ul>

