<h2>16.3 Branch Delete Rules</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Branches are <b>soft-deleted</b> (is_active = 0), not physically removed</li>
  <li>Cannot delete the last active branch — server returns 400 error</li>
  <li>Deleted branch data (sales, purchases, inventory) remains in database but becomes inaccessible via normal queries</li>
</ul>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 17. DATABASE SCHEMA -->
<h1>17. Database Schema Reference</h1>

<h2>17.1 Core Tables</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Table</th><th>Primary Key</th><th>Key Columns</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
  <tr><td>organizations</td><td>id</td><td>name, code (UNIQUE), type, address, phone, email, currency, is_active</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>branches</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, name, code, address, phone, email, is_active</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>users</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, branch_id (NULL=org_admin), name, email, phone, password_hash, role, is_active</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>settings</td><td>(organization_id, key)</td><td>organization_id, key, value</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>customers</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, code, name, phone, email, address</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>suppliers</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, code, name, phone, email, address</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>tires</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, branch_id, brand, model, size, tire_type_id, stock, reorder_level, cost_price, sale_price</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>products</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, code, name, category, unit, cost_price, sale_price, description, is_active</td><td>Org</td></tr>
  <tr><td>tire_types</td><td>id</td><td>organization_id, name</td><td>Org</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>17.2 Transactional Tables</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Table</th><th>Foreign Keys</th><th>Key Columns</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
  <tr><td>sales</td><td>customer_id, organization_id, branch_id</td><td>invoice_no, date, subtotal, tax, total, amount_paid, status, notes</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>sale_items</td><td>sale_id, tire_id, product_id</td><td>tire_name, qty, unit_price, amount</td><td>via sale</td></tr>
  <tr><td>sale_payments</td><td>sale_id, customer_id, organization_id, branch_id</td><td>amount, payment_date, payment_method, reference_no, notes</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>purchases</td><td>supplier_id, organization_id, branch_id</td><td>po_no, date, subtotal, tax, total, amount_paid, status, notes</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>purchase_items</td><td>purchase_id, tire_id, product_id</td><td>tire_name, qty, unit_price, amount</td><td>via purchase</td></tr>
  <tr><td>purchase_payments</td><td>purchase_id, supplier_id, organization_id, branch_id</td><td>amount, payment_date, payment_method, reference_no, notes</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
  <tr><td>ledger_entries</td><td>organization_id, branch_id, entity_id, sale_id, purchase_id</td><td>entry_date, entity_type, entry_type, debit, credit, description, reference_no</td><td>Org+Branch</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 18. API REFERENCE -->
<h1>18. API Endpoints Reference</h1>
<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>Description</th><th>Headers Required</th></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/auth/register</td><td>Create org + branch + admin user</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/auth/login</td><td>Authenticate and return user+org context</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/organizations</td><td>List all organizations</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/organizations/:id</td><td>Get org with branches</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/organizations</td><td>Create org + first branch</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PUT</td><td>/api/organizations/:id</td><td>Update org</td><td>–</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/branches</td><td>List branches for caller's org</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/branches</td><td>Create branch</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PUT</td><td>/api/branches/:id</td><td>Update branch</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>DELETE</td><td>/api/branches/:id</td><td>Soft-delete branch</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/PUT/DELETE</td><td>/api/customers</td><td>CRUD customers (org-scoped)</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/PUT/DELETE</td><td>/api/suppliers</td><td>CRUD suppliers (org-scoped)</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/PUT/DELETE</td><td>/api/inventory</td><td>CRUD tires (org+branch scoped)</td><td>X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/DELETE</td><td>/api/sales</td><td>CRUD sales (org+branch scoped)</td><td>X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PATCH</td><td>/api/sales/:id/status</td><td>Update sale status</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/DELETE</td><td>/api/purchases</td><td>CRUD purchases (org+branch scoped)</td><td>X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>PATCH</td><td>/api/purchases/:id/status</td><td>Update PO status</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/payments/sale</td><td>Record payment on sale</td><td>X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/payments/sale/:saleId</td><td>Get payments for a sale</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>DELETE</td><td>/api/payments/sale/:id</td><td>Delete sale payment (reverses status)</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/payments/purchase</td><td>Record payment on purchase</td><td>X-Org-ID, X-Branch-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ledger/summary</td><td>Org-level receivable/payable summary</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ledger/customers</td><td>All customers with balances</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ledger/suppliers</td><td>All suppliers with balances</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ledger/customer/:id/statement</td><td>Full statement for customer</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ledger/supplier/:id/statement</td><td>Full statement for supplier</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/settings</td><td>Get org settings (key-value map)</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/settings</td><td>Upsert org settings</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/PUT/DELETE</td><td>/api/products</td><td>CRUD products</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET/POST/PUT/DELETE</td><td>/api/lookups/tire-types</td><td>CRUD tire types</td><td>X-Org-ID</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 19. WORKFLOWS -->
<h1>19. Business Workflow Diagrams</h1>

<h2>19.1 Complete Sale Workflow</h2>
<div class="mockup">
[Customer walks in]
       │
       ▼
[Sales → New Sale]
       │
       ├── Select Customer (existing or create new)
       ├── Add line items (tires from inventory + products)
       ├── Set date, tax, status
       └── Save
              │
              ▼
     [Invoice created]
     ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
     │ • stock decremented per tire line item       │
     │ • Invoice No auto-generated (INV-YYYY-NNN)  │
     │ • status = default_sale_status (e.g. pending)│
     └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
              │
              ▼
     [Customer pays (later)]
     [Sales → CreditCard Icon → Record Payment]
              │
              ├── Enter amount, date, method, reference
              └── Save
                     │
                     ▼
            [Payment recorded]
            ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐
            │ • sale_payments row inserted           │
            │ • ledger_entries credit row inserted   │
            │ • sales.amount_paid updated            │
            │ • sales.status updated:                │
            │   - paid (amount ≥ total)              │
            │   - partial (0 < amount < total)       │
            └────────────────────────────────────────┘</div>

<h2>19.2 Purchase Order Workflow</h2>
<div class="mockup">
[Purchases → New Purchase]
       │
       ├── Select Supplier
       ├── Add line items (tires + products)
       ├── Set date, status = pending
       └── Save (PO-YYYY-NNN assigned)
              │
              ▼
     [Goods arrive at warehouse]
     [Purchases → 📦 Mark as Received]
              │
              ▼
     [Status → received]
     [stock += qty for each tire line item]
              │
              ▼
     [Pay supplier]
     [Purchases → 💳 Record Payment]
              │
              ▼
     [Payment recorded]
     [purchase_payments inserted + ledger_entries debit]</div>

<h2>19.3 New Organization Registration Workflow</h2>
<div class="mockup">
[Visit /auth → Register tab]
       │
       ├── Enter: Full Name, Email, Phone
       ├── Enter: Business Name, Business Type
       ├── Enter: City/Address, Password x2
       └── Accept Terms → Create Account
              │
              ▼
     [Server processes registration]
     1. Validate all inputs
     2. Check email uniqueness
     3. Generate org code from business name
     4. INSERT organizations
     5. INSERT branches (Main Branch / MAIN)
     6. Seed 12 default settings rows
     7. Hash password (bcrypt 12 rounds)
     8. INSERT users (role=org_admin, branch_id=NULL)
     9. Return { success, organization_id, branch_id }
              │
              ▼
     [Frontend shows "Account created!" for 1.8s]
              │
              ▼
     [Auto-redirect to Login]
              │
              ▼
     [Login with new credentials]
              │
              ▼
     [Server returns full context]
     [orgId + branchId saved to localStorage]
     [App renders with org context]</div>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 20. QA TEST PLAN -->
