<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ 21. LIMITATIONS -->
<h1>21. Known Limitations &amp; Workarounds</h1>

<h2>21.1 Current Limitations</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Limitation</th><th>Workaround</th><th>Future Fix</th></tr>
  <tr><td>L-01</td><td>No JWT / session token — login state is in-memory React state only</td><td>Reload page clears login; user must re-login</td><td>Implement JWT with refresh tokens</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-02</td><td>No per-user role enforcement on the API — all authenticated users of an org can access all org data</td><td>Org structure separates data; role displayed but not enforced API-side</td><td>Add role middleware to routes</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-03</td><td>Branch switching requires logout/login — orgId/branchId are set at login and not changeable in-session</td><td>Logout and log back in to switch branch context</td><td>Add branch switcher in header dropdown</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-04</td><td>Ledger statements are org-wide; cannot filter by single branch</td><td>View full org history (complete account picture)</td><td>Add ?branch_id query param to statement endpoints</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-05</td><td>No real-time notifications — notification counts load once on login</td><td>Refresh page or navigate away and back to update counts</td><td>Add WebSocket or polling</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-06</td><td>Invoice numbering counter is based on total count, not sequential per year</td><td>Gaps can appear if records are deleted</td><td>Implement sequence table for invoice numbering</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-07</td><td>Google Sign-In integration requires VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID env variable</td><td>Button shows placeholder; use email/password login</td><td>Configure Google OAuth client ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-08</td><td>PDF generation is client-side — large invoices with many line items may have rendering delays</td><td>Invoice automatically downloads when ready</td><td>Server-side PDF generation</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-09</td><td>No file/image upload for company logo in settings</td><td>Company initial letter avatar used instead</td><td>Add S3/file upload for logo</td></tr>
  <tr><td>L-10</td><td>Bulk import errors don't download as a report</td><td>Errors are shown in a modal dialog after import</td><td>Export error report as Excel</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>21.2 Critical Route Order Note</h2>
<div class="warn"><b>Important for developers:</b> In Express.js routes that have both <code>GET /bulk</code> and <code>GET /:id</code> endpoints, the <code>/bulk</code> route MUST be registered before <code>/:id</code>. If registered after, Express treats "bulk" as an ID parameter and the bulk endpoint returns "not found". This applies to: customers, suppliers, inventory, sales, purchases routes.</div>

<h2>21.3 Settings Table PK Migration Note</h2>
<div class="note"><b>Note:</b> The settings table's primary key was migrated from a single-column PK on <code>[key]</code> to a compound PK on <code>(organization_id, [key])</code>. The migration script in <code>db.js</code> dynamically finds and drops the auto-named PK constraint before creating the new compound one. This is idempotent and safe to run multiple times.</div>

<h2>21.4 Data Backfill</h2>
<div class="info"><b>Backward compatibility:</b> All multi-tenancy columns (<code>organization_id</code>, <code>branch_id</code>) were added with <code>NOT NULL DEFAULT 1</code>. Any data that existed before the multi-tenancy migration is automatically assigned to Organization ID = 1 and Branch ID = 1, ensuring zero data loss and continued operation for single-organization deployments.</div>

